description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Clinical Assistant Administrator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Eastbourne&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;£17,500 - £18,500&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working pattern: &lt;/strong&gt;36 hours per week, on a shift/rota basis from Monday to Sunday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;InHealth sees more than 3 million patients each year and diagnostic imaging is one of the busiest services we provide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for a &lt;strong&gt;Clinical Assistant Administrator &lt;/strong&gt;to join our MRI radiographydepartment at &lt;strong&gt;Eastbourne District General Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the overall purpose of the job?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Clinical AssistantAdministrator,you will act as a first point of contact for all visitors, patients and incoming calls. You will be responsible for working on the receptionist desk, greeting patients in a welcoming manner, preparing them for their procedure and assisting with any questions they may have. You will also complete some administrative tasks within the department for clinical practitioners, enabling the team to deliver effective and efficient patient care whilst maintaining a safe clinical environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are the key responsibilities of the role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Greeting patients and their carers in an empathetic and professional manner, ensuring their arrival is correctly recorded on the patient administration system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answering the reception telephone in a professional manner ensuring all issues/messages are escalated to the manager or appropriate person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring that clinically validated appointments are booked appropriately and according to clinical priority on the appointments system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring all patients are invoiced promptly and accurately and that payment is taken on the day, recorded and banked promptly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting in the completion of month end administrative procedures for the management team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing patients for their procedure and escorting them to the clinical area as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clarifying patient’s identification and completing the pre-scan consent and data protection form as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing and monitoring the patient’s condition post procedure, ensuring any changes and concerns are reported to the relevant staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What skills and experience will you need to apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working within a customer or patient focused environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using Microsoft packages and other IT systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for delivering the highest level of customer service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with a capability to present information in a logical manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong administration skills with an ability to pick up new systems quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can InHealth offer you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a highly competitive salary and a generous flexible benefits package, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days holiday plus bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private medical healthcare&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible benefits (inc discounted gym membership, dental care)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plus much more!&lt;/p&gt;
